# Default — product team owns everything not explicitly matched below
* @onterris/PRODUCT_TEAM

# ── Workflow files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STRICTEST gate. The OIDC token for the Apply SP is issued inside these files.
# A single-line workflow change can exfiltrate the token and own the subscription.
# Require both BU leads AND platform team on every change, including 1-line diffs.
/.github/                   @onterris/PRODUCT_LEADS @onterris/platform-team

# ── L1 Core — platform-facing configuration ───────────────────────────────────
# Hub peering, IPAM pool consumption, DNS zone links, and baseline NSG rules
# are platform-owned. The platform team is the accountable owner for these paths.
/core/platform/             @onterris/platform-team

# BU-owned core (subnets, app-internal NSGs, NAT GW, UAMIs).
# Platform team is required reviewer (catches policy violations, address-space
# conflicts, posture drift) but the product team is the accountable owner.
/core/bu/                   @onterris/PRODUCT_TEAM @onterris/platform-team

# ── L5 Edge — WAF policy and Front Door ───────────────────────────────────────
# Edge changes are product-team-owned but require platform review because
# WAF rules and Front Door origin config affect the blast radius of a compromise.
/edge/                      @onterris/PRODUCT_TEAM @onterris/platform-team
